==Demographics==
Serena first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2020 U.S. census]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=2020 Geography Changes|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/acs/technical-documentation/table-and-geography-changes/2020/geography-changes.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |access-date=}}</ref>

As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/profile?g=1600000US1768679 |access-date=2022-06-28 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref> there were 129 people, 4 households, and 4 families residing in the CDP. The population density was {{convert|524.39|PD/sqmi|PD/km2}}. There were 59 housing units at an average density of {{convert|239.84|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}. The racial makeup of the CDP was 89.92% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 2.33% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.78% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 2.33% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], and 4.65% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 6.20% of the population.

